{"questionId":"3559602","questionHtml":"<p>State the hypotheses for the test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The hypotheses may be written in words but must include reference to the mean (e.g. “number of snails” is not sufficient to award <em><strong>A1</strong></em>), and state clearly for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> that the mean increases.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3559602","referenceCode":"23M.2.AHL.TZ2.6e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the hypotheses for the test.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}